==Usage==
; Normal usage (icon and link)
<pre>
{{Infobox/socials
| type = type_code
| link = link_url
| description
}}
</pre>

; No link usage (icon without link)
<pre>
{{Infobox/socials
| type = type_code
| description
}}
</pre>

; Default link usage (generic link icon)
<pre>
{{Infobox/socials
| link = link_url
| description
}}
</pre>

; Page link
<pre>
{{Infobox/socials
| type = type_code
| page = page name
| description
}}
</pre>

; Custom icon and no link
<pre>
{{Infobox/socials
| icon = File:file_name.extension
| description
}}
</pre>

===Parameters===
;{{Code|type}} {{Sup|Mutual exclusive|green}}
: The type of social media icon to display. Valid options are:
* discord
* steam
* github
* bitbucket
* X
* forum
* blog
* gdrive
* npmjs
: To add new ones, please edit the Lua module dataset {{ll|Module:Socials/data}}.
;{{Code|link}} {{Sup|Mutual exclusive|orange}}
: The URL to link to. If not provided, no link will be added.
;{{Code|page}} {{Sup|Mutual exclusive|orange}}
: The name of a wiki page to link to.
;{{Code|icon}} {{Sup|Mutual exclusive|green}}
: A custom icon file to use instead of the default social media icons. The icon should be in the format {{Code|File:file_name.extension}}.
;{{Code|1}}
: The description text to display next to the icon.

{{Note|All parameters are technically optional, and are needed only based on the use case.}}
}}

